<TITLE> 21 workers killed in Gazipur garments fire</font> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)Twenty-one garment workers, mostly women, were killed as a fire blazed through a sweater factory in Gazipur on Thursday night, police and emergency workers said. Dhaka fire control room duty officer Nazrul Islam told bdnews24.com firefighters at one point handed 22 "unconscious" bodies, reportedly suffering smoke inhalation, to Gazipur Sadar Police Station. The fire broke out at around 9.30pm at Garib & Garib Sweater Factory at the 'Four Road' intersection in Bhogra, Gazipur. Islam said around 10 fire units and six ambulances rushed to the scene. It took two hours to douse the flames, but firemen were still 'dumping down' at 1.30am on Friday. Factory worker Sumon told bdnews24.com the fire started on the first floor of the seven-storey building as workers had finished for the night and were leaving the factory. He said several workers were stuck on the second floor as the fire spread. "Firemen had to cut the window grills to rescue them." None on the scene could immediately say how many workers had been in the building. Joydebpur police station officer in charge Abdur Rashid said at least 50 were injured, suffering burns or smoke inhalation. Of them, 20-25 were taken to Gazipur General Hospital at around 11.45pm. Gazipur General Hospital's emergency department's Dr Md Ataul Islam told bdnews24.com: "Around 20 people were brought in, of which 11 were pronounced dead." Another seven workers were taken to Tongi Government Hospital where they were pronounced dead, the emergency unit's Dr Mamun or Rashid told bdnews24.com. Doctors at Tairunnessa Memorial Medical College and Hospital confirmed another three fire victims had died there. Of the dead, 15 were women workers were, six were men. bdne
